Total in Talks to Sell 800 U.K. Retail Sites to Investor Group, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-04-04T00:35:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/total-in-talks-to-sell-800-u-k-retail-sites-to-investor-group-ft-says.html
A group of investors, including
Gerald Ronson, property developer and founder of gasoline retail
chain Snax 24,  Investec Ltd. (INL)  and Grovepoint Capital, are holding
exclusive discussions with  Total SA (FP)  about buying about 800 U.K.
gas stations, the Financial Times reported, without attribution.  The deal for the stations, that make almost 10 percent of
the market, could be valued at about 400 million pounds ($645
million), the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 